&gt;Let's point out that *.UUCP should NOT map into a silent forwarding to
&gt;uunet.uu.net, which is not advertised as providing such a service.

I agree.  I have never used uunet as a forwarder for unknown (to me)
UUCP hosts, but when I do happen to want to send mail to/through uunet
I now have a CNAME RR that equates "uunet.UUCP" with "uunet.UU.NET",
and the mail will be routed appropriately.  This should bother no one.

                        :: Jeff Makey
                           Makey@Logicon.COM

